name: fingerprint
description: the 9th sigil. once a reliable method for quantizing and tracking humans, biometrics quickly became controversial once artificially intelligent beings were given equal rights to humans. bionic entities fought diligently for a new standard for personal identification, eventually leading to the widespread adoption of non-fungible fingerprints like these. collect to attract singularity. inscribed by tenorless circa 2019 // genesis collection [contribution to OBJKT4OBJKT weekend april 2021]
